programme.desc: A white family in the Texas panhandle is at the center of controversy because they have an adopted Kiowa child, and there is a great amount of tension in the town between those two races. When the secret goes public, a war begins.

programme.title: McLintock!
programme.desc: Story of an aging cattle baron and his divorce-minded wife, who walked out on him two years ago without a word of explanation and has been living back East and running in very fancy circles.

programme.title: Firecreek
programme.desc: A peace-loving sheriff defends his small town against an outlaw gang. The sheriff, who only works part time, first attempts to stay out the gang's way, but as their brutish behavior escalates, he must take a stand.

programme.title: The Rounders
programme.desc: Two aging but freewheeling horse wranglers dreaming of better days and hoping to make enough money to retire enter their wild, stubborn roan, who has a taste for alcohol, in a bucking-bronco contest at a rodeo.

programme.title: The Longest Night
programme.desc: Mayhem, murders and romance in a department store. Joan: Florence Rice. Charley: Robert Young. Sergeant: Ted Healy. Mrs. Briggs: Janet Beecher. Mrs. Wilson: Catherine Doucet.

programme.title: Love in the Rough
programme.desc: At a country-club golf tournament, an heiress (Dorothy Jordan) meets a shipping clerk (Robert Montgomery) reputed to be president of a corporation. Virgie: Dorothy McNulty (Penny Singleton). Benny: Benny Rubin. Waters: J.C. Nugent. Johnson: Allan Lane. Directed by Charles F. Riesner.

programme.title: Looking Forward
programme.desc: A family owned business falls on hard times over the years, leading to various stories of both success and failure for everyone connected to it.

programme.title: Going Places
programme.desc: A sporting-goods salesman with a fear of horses poses as a famous rider in an effort to make more sales, leading to many wacky misunderstandings.

programme.title: Two Hearts in Wax Time
programme.desc: Musical short about a tipsy department-store worker (Gus Shy) who imagines his showroom mannequins have come to life to perform song-and-dance routines. Frank Hayes, Shirley Ross.

programme.title: There Goes My Heart
programme.desc: A reporter (Fredric March) tracing a runaway rich girl (Virginia Bruce) finds her---working in her own department store. Eugene Pallette, Patsy Kelly, Nancy Carroll, Alan Mowbray, Claude Gillingwater, Arthur Lake, Harry Langdon. Norman Z. McLeod directed.

programme.title: Sweepings
programme.desc: A self-made man builds up a successful department store empire after the Chicago fire. He wants to leave the business to his sons and daughter, but confronts their lack of interest and ability.

programme.title: Our Blushing Brides
programme.desc: A tale of the lives and loves of three female roommates trying to make it in the Big Apple. One works as a department-store mannequin, while the other two are clerks.

programme.title: Employees' Entrance
programme.desc: The goings-on of a ruthless store manager and the people around him.

programme.title: The Big Store

programme.title: The Beloved Rogue
programme.desc: John Barrymore displays top romantic form in this costume tale. The setting is 15th-century France: Barrymore plays Francois Villon, the poet-thief whose legend inspired Rudolf Friml's operetta "The Vagabond King." Louis XI: Conrad Veidt. Charlotte: Marceline Day. Thibault: Henry Victor. Nicholas: Mack Swain. John: Lawson Butt.

programme.title: The First Degree

programme.title: Beverly of Graustark

programme.title: Irving Thalberg: Prince of Hollywood
programme.desc: A profile of the wunderkind producer includes clips and stills from his productions, plus new and archival interviews with film historian Cari Beauchamp, Samuel Goldwyn Jr. and journalist Bob Thomas. Stanley Tucci narrates. The documentary was produced, written and directed by Robert Trachtenberg.

programme.title: He Who Gets Slapped

programme.title: Ten Nights in a Barroom
programme.desc: An alcoholic has several devastating encounters that propel him to stop drinking and become mayor.

programme.title: Ramona
programme.desc: Escaping her cruel and judgmental guardian, Ramona sadly resigns herself to the probability that she will never find true happiness because she is a half-breed. Though she loves Moreno's grandson Felipe, Ramona does not want him to bear the stigma of a mixed marriage, so she marries Allesandro, an Indian shepherd. Misfortune continues to befall the heroine when her husband is lynched by bigoted white ranchers.

programme.title: Nanook of the North

programme.title: Haxan: Witchcraft Through the Ages

programme.title: Out Yonder
